            . I have known the prisoner from a child; she visited me on the 15th and 16th of November, and drank tea on each occasion, and on the morning of the 17th I missed four silver spoons.</p>
               <p>THOMAS FRUGIE (Police-constable D 161). I apprehended the prisoner in Chapel-street; I told her what I took her for - she made on answer; the prosecutor said to her at the watch-house, "Mary, have you sold my spoons?" she said No, but she had pawned them in Skinner-street -I found two of them.</p>
